<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="330" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="94.[151,756,558,1026]" pageId="94" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,264,558,582]" pageId="94" pageNumber="330">Remarks:</emphasis>
When splitting the former Family 
<taxonomicName authority=", Lindsay et al. (2017)" authorityName="Lindsay" authorityYear="2017" class="Hydrozoa" family="Aeginidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Narcomedusae" pageId="94" pageNumber="330" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">
Aeginidae, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lindsay" box="[151,390,589,614]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Lindsay" pageId="94" pageNumber="330" pagination="494 - 512" refId="ref70828" refString="Lindsay D. J., Grossmann M. M., Bentlage B., Collins A. G., Minemizu R., Hopcroft R. R., Miyake H., Hidaka-Umetsu M., Nishikawa J. 2017. The perils of online biogeographic databases: a case study with the ' monospecific' genus Aegina (Cnidaria, Hydrozoa, Narcomedusae). Marine Biology Research 13 (5): 494 - 512." type="journal article" year="2017">
Lindsay 
<emphasis box="[249,300,589,613]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="330">et al</emphasis>
. (2017)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
proposed this new family name based on their new genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindsay" authorityYear="2017" box="[441,607,621,645]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Solmundaeginidae" genus="Solmundaegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Narcomedusae" pageId="94" pageNumber="330" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[441,607,621,645]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="330">Solmundaegina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and included also the other genera listed above. They may have overlooked that by including the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Haeckel, 1879" authorityName="Haeckel" authorityYear="1879" class="Hydrozoa" family="Solmundaeginidae" genus="Solmundus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Narcomedusae" pageId="94" pageNumber="330" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[637,756,685,709]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="330">Solmundus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Haeckel" box="[151,308,716,740]" firstAuthor="Haeckel" pageId="94" pageNumber="330" pagination="1 - 360" refId="ref68751" refString="Haeckel E. 1879. Das System der Medusen. Erster Teil einer Monographie der Medusen. Denkschriften der Medicinisch- Naturwissenschaftlichen Gesellschaft zu Jena 1: I-XX, 1 - 360, 20 pls." type="book chapter" year="1879">Haeckel, 1879</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
there is already a family level name for this group available, namely the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authority="Haeckel, 1879" authorityName="Haeckel" authorityYear="1879" class="Hydrozoa" family="Cuninidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Narcomedusae" pageId="94" pageNumber="330" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Solmundinae">
Solmundinae 
<bibRefCitation author="Haeckel" box="[151,309,780,804]" firstAuthor="Haeckel" pageId="94" pageNumber="330" pagination="1 - 360" refId="ref68751" refString="Haeckel E. 1879. Das System der Medusen. Erster Teil einer Monographie der Medusen. Denkschriften der Medicinisch- Naturwissenschaftlichen Gesellschaft zu Jena 1: I-XX, 1 - 360, 20 pls." type="book chapter" year="1879">Haeckel, 1879</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which is also valid at the family level as Solmundidae 
<bibRefCitation author="Haeckel" box="[304,467,811,836]" firstAuthor="Haeckel" pageId="94" pageNumber="330" pagination="1 - 360" refId="ref68751" refString="Haeckel E. 1879. Das System der Medusen. Erster Teil einer Monographie der Medusen. Denkschriften der Medicinisch- Naturwissenschaftlichen Gesellschaft zu Jena 1: I-XX, 1 - 360, 20 pls." type="book chapter" year="1879">Haeckel, 1879</bibRefCitation>
. However, we agree with 
<bibRefCitation author="Lindsay" box="[151,376,843,867]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Lindsay" pageId="94" pageNumber="330" pagination="494 - 512" refId="ref70828" refString="Lindsay D. J., Grossmann M. M., Bentlage B., Collins A. G., Minemizu R., Hopcroft R. R., Miyake H., Hidaka-Umetsu M., Nishikawa J. 2017. The perils of online biogeographic databases: a case study with the ' monospecific' genus Aegina (Cnidaria, Hydrozoa, Narcomedusae). Marine Biology Research 13 (5): 494 - 512." type="journal article" year="2017">
Lindsay 
<emphasis box="[244,299,843,867]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="330">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
that the 
<typeStatus box="[472,518,844,868]" pageId="94" pageNumber="330">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haeckel" authorityYear="1879" box="[639,756,843,867]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Solmundaeginidae" genus="Solmundus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Narcomedusae" pageId="94" pageNumber="330" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[639,756,843,867]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="330">Solmundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Haeckel, 1879" authorityName="Haeckel" authorityYear="1879" box="[160,480,875,899]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Solmundaeginidae" genus="Solmundus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Narcomedusae" pageId="94" pageNumber="330" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="tetralinus">
<emphasis box="[160,300,875,899]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="330">S. tetralinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Haeckel" box="[315,480,875,899]" firstAuthor="Haeckel" pageId="94" pageNumber="330" pagination="1 - 360" refId="ref68751" refString="Haeckel E. 1879. Das System der Medusen. Erster Teil einer Monographie der Medusen. Denkschriften der Medicinisch- Naturwissenschaftlichen Gesellschaft zu Jena 1: I-XX, 1 - 360, 20 pls." type="book chapter" year="1879">Haeckel, 1879</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) is a doubtful species, perhaps an aberrant 
<taxonomicName box="[398,692,907,931]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Solmundaeginidae" genus="Solmundella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Narcomedusae" pageId="94" pageNumber="330" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="bitentaculata">
<emphasis box="[398,692,907,931]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="330">Solmundella bitentaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with four tentacles. Family names should not be based on dubious genera and species and it is advisable to remove 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haeckel" authorityYear="1879" box="[151,268,1002,1026]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Solmundaeginidae" genus="Solmundus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Narcomedusae" pageId="94" pageNumber="330" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,268,1002,1026]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="330">Solmundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindsay, Bentlage &amp; Collins" authorityYear="2017" box="[373,575,1002,1026]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Solmundaeginidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Narcomedusae" pageId="94" pageNumber="330" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Solmundaeginidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
